The ANC says it will take the newly-amended step-aside resolution to the branches. The move comes after the party's Treasurer General Paul Mashatile said the step-aside rule will now only apply going forward. eNCA's Pule Letshwiti-Jones reports. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The ANC says it will take the newly-amended step-aside resolution to the branches. The move comes after the party's Treasurer General Paul Mashatile said the step-aside rule will now only apply going forward. WATCH | ANC clarifies step-aside policy Mashatile said the step-aside decision won't affect those who have already been elected in ANC conferences. Its application is not retrospective. * eNCA's Pule Letshwiti-Jones reports.